**Repository:** [github.com/ST10247932/Spottr](https://github.com/ST10247932/PROG3D-Community-Reporter-App.git)

Spottr is an Android application designed to help users **report, view, and track incidents** happening in their area in real time.  
By combining secure authentication, a live map, and insightful data visualization, Spottr empowers communities to stay informed and safe.

---

## ğŸ§­ Purpose of the App

The purpose of **Spottr** is to provide a **centralized and interactive platform** where users can:
- **Report incidents** such as crimes, safety hazards, or emergencies in real time.
- **View incidents** on an interactive **map**, updated automatically via an API.
- **Analyze data** through visual graphs showing incident trends and types in different locations.
- **Receive alerts and notifications** based on user preferences and location.
- **Manage personal information** through a dedicated profile and settings page.

This helps **bridge communication** between users and local authorities by improving **incident visibility** and **community awareness**.

---

## ğŸ¨ Design Considerations

### ğŸ”’ Security and Privacy
- Registration and login via **Secure Single Sign-On (SSO)**.
- All data stored securely in **Firebase Firestore**.
- Reports contain **timestamps** and **geolocation** for reliability.

### ğŸŒ User Interface (UI/UX)
- Designed using **Material Design 3** principles.
- Easy navigation with a bottom navigation bar.
- Maps, charts, and reports visually integrated for clarity.

### ğŸ§± Architecture
- **Kotlin-based Android app**.
- **Firebase Firestore** for cloud data storage.
- **Google Maps API** for displaying incidents.
- **MVVM architecture** for better scalability and maintenance.

---

## ğŸ“± App Features

### ğŸ  Home Page
- Displays a **detailed live map** showing all reported incidents (via API).
- Users can filter incidents by type or date.

### ğŸ§¾ Add Report
- Users can submit detailed incident reports.
- Includes **description, category, location, and timestamp**.
- Automatically logs to Firestore and updates the live map.

### ğŸ“Š Graphs Page
- Visualizes **incident data trends** using charts (e.g., bar, pie).
- Pulls data from the backend API to stay updated.

### ğŸ”” Alerts & Notifications
- Users can **toggle alerts on/off**.
- Choose **sound, vibration**, and **priority level**.
- Customizable through both the Alerts shortcut and Settings page.

### ğŸ‘¤ Profile Page
- Shows user information and allows profile updates.

### âš™ï¸ Settings Page
- Manage **alerts**, **privacy policy**, and **location settings**.
- Toggle app permissions using system settings.

### ğŸ•’ History Page
- Displays **previously submitted reports**.
- Acts as a personal activity log for user reference.

